                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/709</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Phillips</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-29">July 29,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I discussed at considerable length this afternoon with the President the question
                    of the appointment of a Financial Adviser to China. He is still not ready to say
                    “yes” or “no”, and believes that our best answer for the present is to reply
                    that the matter is still under advisement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
